data.enText: a situation in which all activity or movement has stopped

data.chText: 安全警戒使机场陷入停顿状态。
data.enText: The security alert brought the airport to a standstill .

data.chText: 北行车道的交通完全堵塞。
data.enText: Traffic in the northbound lane is at a complete standstill .

ex.enText: It is difficult to break the deadlock.
The negotiation has reached a deadlock.

synonyms.bx: 指双方未能就分歧达成协议的僵持局面。

ex.enText: The argument came to a halt.

ex.chText: 大雨迫使马拉松比赛暂停。
ex.enText: Heavy rain brought the marathon to a temporary halt.

synonyms.bx: 尤指活动的突然或被迫终止。

ex.chText: 与反对派的商谈以陷入僵局而告终。
ex.enText: The discussions with the opposition group ended in a stalemate.

ex.chText: 这盘国际象棋比赛以和棋结束。
ex.enText: The chess game ended in a stalemate.

synonyms.bx: 指争论双方难以解决争议或分歧，谁也无法占上风；也可指国际象棋中的僵局、和棋。

ex.enText: Heavy fog brought the traffic to a standstill.

synonyms.bx: 指没有任何运动或活动的状态。

tr: a situation in which no progress can be made or no advancement is possible
example: reached an impasse on the negotiations

value.def: If movement or activity comes to or is brought to a standstill, it stops completely.

example.ex: Abruptly the group ahead of us came to a standstill...
example.tran: 我们前面的小组突然停了下来。

example.ex: Production is more or less at a standstill.
example.tran: 生产几乎处于停顿状态。

trans: 停止；停滞不前；止步不前；停顿；停滞
